<HL>
   Business Brief -- Information International Inc.:
   Litigation With Publisher
   Over Software Is Settled
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8A
</SO>
<CO>
   IINT
</CO>
<LP>
   Information International Inc. said it settled certain
litigation with Morris Communications Corp. over computer
software used for newspaper publishing and commercial
printing.
   Under the settlements, which dealt with suits filed last
October in federal court in Georgia, Morris Communications
withdrew demands for restitution of the $3 million purchase
price of a software system bought from Information
International. For its part, Information International paid
royalty payments owed to Morris on separate software acquired
from Morris.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Information International, based in Culver City, Calif.,
makes computer software for the publishing business, among
others. Closely held Morris Communications, based in Augusta,
Ga., is a newspaper publishing concern.
</TEXT>
